’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Grosvenor was born in 1500, in Bellaport, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas (Grosvenor) le Grosvenor, was 123 and his mother, Joan (Venables) Grosvenor, was 116. He had at least 1 son with Isabelle (Peshale) Grosvenor. He died in 1569, at the age of 69."},"et":{"1500–1569":"1500–1569","1414–Female":"1414–Surnud","1455–1522":"1455–1522","1377–1430":"1377–1430","1384–1432":"1384–1432","1569":"1569","1414":"1414","1500":"1500","1522":"1522","1455":"1455","1432":"1432","1377":"1377","1430":"1430","1384":"1384","1 March 1522":"1. märts 1522","Bellaport, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bellaport, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bellaport, Shropshire, England":"Bellaport, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1500–1569":"1500–1569","1414–Female":"1414–Kuollut","1455–1522":"1455–1522","1377–1430":"1377–1430","1384–1432":"1384–1432","1569":"1569","1414":"1414","1500":"1500","1522":"1522","1455":"1455","1432":"1432","1377":"1377","1430":"1430","1384":"1384","1 March 1522":"1. maaliskuuta 1522","Bellaport, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bellaport, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bellaport, Shropshire, England":"Bellaport, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1500–1569":"1500–1569","1414–Female":"1414–Décédée","1455–1522":"1455–1522","1377–1430":"1377–1430","1384–1432":"1384–1432","1569":"1569","1414":"1414","1500":"1500","1522":"1522","1455":"1455","1432":"1432","1377":"1377","1430":"1430","1384":"1384","1 March 1522":"1 mars 1522","Bellaport, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bellaport, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Bellaport, Shropshire, England":"Bellaport, Sh